Muhammad Nana is Mastercard’s VP of Fintech, Enabler, and PSP Partnerships for the EEMEA region. He has over 6 years of experience at Mastercard and has also worked at leading South African companies like MTN and Standard Bank. Nana has extensive knowledge of the payments processing industry and has delivered many complex projects for this environment. He is passionate about the mobile payments industry and believes that this is the future of payments. In this conference session, Nana explains how Mastercard leveraged its dominant position in the payments industry to become a leader in the FinTech space, too. He then highlights the major trends and challenges that Mastercard is seeing in the FinTech industry. Nana also discusses Mastercard’s launch of Fintech Express in the Middle East and Africa region and explains what this program is all about. He expands on the three core modules of Fintech Express and concludes by highlighting what sets this program apart from other solutions on the market. The full interview with Muhammad Nana can be viewed below. 